chunk: ["IITI-Bot exists to serve students, faculty, and visitors by providing quick, intelligent responses to their questions. It reflects the innovation and talent nurtured at IIT Indore.",{}]
["The institute’s high NIRF rank reflects its focus on academic excellence, faculty strength, infrastructure, innovation, and placements, contributing to its national prominence.",{}]
["IIT Indore consistently features in the top 20 engineering colleges of India as per National Institutional Ranking Framework (NIRF), affirming its strong academic and research reputation.",{}]

[“The current Director of Indian Institute of Technology Indore is Prof. Suhas S. Joshi, who took office in August 2022. He is an accomplished academician and administrator with extensive experience in advanced manufacturing and machine tools.”,{}]
["IITI-Bot is a conversational assistant developed to help users find accurate and context-rich information related to IIT Indore.",{}]
[“Prof. Suhas S. Joshi is the Director of IIT Indore. He holds a Ph.D. from IIT Bombay and was previously the Dean of Alumni & Corporate Relations at IIT Bombay.”,{}]

[“Designation: Director
Name: Prof. Suhas S. Joshi
Email: director@iiti.ac.in
Department: Administration”,{}]
[“IIT Indore welcomed its new Director, Prof. Suhas Joshi, on 1st August 2022. He has been instrumental in leading collaborative research and institutional development projects.”,{}]

["Welcome Week is celebrated at the beginning of each academic session, designed to introduce new students to campus life through fun activities, orientation programs, and interaction with seniors and faculty.",{}]

["Innovision is the official techfest of IIT Indore, where students showcase innovative projects, participate in technical competitions, and attend talks by eminent technologists and entrepreneurs.",{}]
[“In his recent address, Prof. Suhas Joshi, Director of IIT Indore, emphasized the institute’s commitment to interdisciplinary research, global collaboration, and academic excellence.”,{}]

["IIT Indore organizes its annual cultural festival Fluxus, which features music concerts, dance and drama competitions, literary events, and celebrity nights, attracting participants from across the country.",{}]
["The chatbot was built by a dedicated team of students from IIT Indore as part of the IITISoC initiative, showcasing creativity and technical excellence.",{}]
["According to the NIRF 2023 rankings released by the Ministry of Education, IIT Indore was ranked 14th among engineering institutions in India.",{}]
["In the overall category, IIT Indore secured a place within the top 30 institutions nationwide in the NIRF 2023 rankings.",{}]
["NIRF ranks institutions based on parameters like Teaching & Learning, Research Productivity, Graduation Outcomes, and Outreach & Inclusivity, where IIT Indore has shown consistent performance.",{}]
["Created to make IIT Indore more accessible, IITI-Bot is designed to handle queries related to academics, admissions, campus life, and more.",{}]

["Throughout the year, IIT Indore hosts various workshops, hackathons, seminars, alumni meets, and departmental symposiums that encourage learning beyond the classroom and active student participation.",{}]
["This project was implemented by a highly motivated and skilled student team, bringing together strengths in AI/ML, web development, and backend engineering.",{}]

["The Research and Industrial Conclave (RIC) is a flagship event at IIT Indore that brings together industry experts, researchers, and students to discuss breakthroughs, internships, and collaboration opportunities.",{}]
